Russian President Vladimir Putin has signed a law on the introduction of administrative liability for violation of the term and order of payment for goods (works, services) in the procurement for State and municipal needs.
This law is intended to solve the very acute problem of non-fulfillment of its obligations by customers in the implementation of State and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation, when businessmen could not get payment on already executed state and municipal contracts, was widespread.
At the same time, the Russian President instructed the Prosecutor General's Office to take the problem to special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers who concluded unfunded contracts, tried in every way to evade the commitments made on payment and included in the contracts illegal conditions.
The problem was systemic in general in the country.
Since 2015, the prosecutor's office has made 9.7 thousand in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders. The results of their consideration to disciplinary responsibility attracted 4.5 thousand. Officials, to administrative-533, the investigative bodies for the organization of procedural checks submitted 75 materials, on 46 of them criminal cases were opened.
As a result, the debt owed to entrepreneurs in the amount of more than 66 billion rubles was liquidated.
And these huge sums were not accumulated as a result of non-payment of multi-billion contracts.
Numerous, systematic delays in payment of services to businessmen on much more modest sums have led to fabulous debts.
This is a typical case.
The head of the small company won the competition for the provision of services on social transportation for several million rubles.
The man has put all his circulating assets, has completely fulfilled obligations, but the put money in time has not received.
The result is a growing financial com from debts on wages, taxes, credits, which would lead to bankruptcy, if the businessman did not appeal to the prosecutor's office for help.
Now in some regions the problem has been maximally neutralize.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of 2017, the total volume of debt under state and municipal contracts, identified by the prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor's office operates in a manual crisis management regime.
The Attorney-General personally conducts on-site meetings with representatives of the local authorities, where all prosecutors ' disclosed violations and measures for their immediate elimination are subject to a substantive hearing.
Such operational meetings have already been held in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg this year.
The implementation of federal law № 189-FZ "On amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences in the part of establishing administrative responsibility will be able to improve qualitatively the payment discipline of public customers" Officials of the customer for violation of the term and order of payment of goods (works, services) in the procurement for the provision of state and municipal needs ", which was signed last week by the president of Russia.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Development of Russia on the initiative of Prosecutor General.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences with the article, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand. Up to 50 thou. Rubles for violation by the official of the customer of the term and order of payment for goods, works and services under state and municipal procurement.
And if an official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation have already received the order to ensure the application of these legislative novels in practice.
