"The evolution of the EPA-after our lawsuits-is an important victory in the fight for health and safety 6.7 million New Yorkers and more than 115 million Americans, who directly influenced the smog, covering their cities,"-said Schneiderman.
New York was joined by California, Connecticut, Delaware, Illinois, Iowa, Maine, Massachusetts, New Mexico, Oregon, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, Vermont and Washington, as well as the District of Columbia.
Ozone at ground level occurs when conventional contaminants from machines, power plants, refineries and chemical plants and other sources enter the atmosphere in response to sunlight.
