Studies have shown that prep significantly reduces the risk of HIV infection among people at risk.
When taking prep before sex in the human body, a sufficient number of certain drugs to prevent HIV infection.
Such drugs can be taken daily or not later than two hours before sex.
The patients eligible for the drug include homosexual and bisexual men, transgender people and those whose partners are HIV-positive and do not receive successful treatment.
