And stretch to Russia, to some extent experiencing nostalgia for it.
Do you believe that the arms embargo imposed on Libya is likely to be lifted soon?
Are your Libyan interlocutors interested in the supply of Russian weapons?
are interested, of course, but, as I said, we do not take sides in this conflict, and do not want to arm some to the detriment of others.
We would like to see everyone in equal positions.
As far as the arms embargo is concerned, there is a constant call on the part of Libyans for Russia to contribute to its withdrawal.
