Electricity cheaper for residents and producers of Buryatia
Lasted decades of efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for consumers of electric energy begin to give fruit.
From September 1, the cost of low voltage electricity for industrial recipients is reduced by 25%.
Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the decree of the Government of the Russian Federation "on amendments to the rules of the wholesale market of electric power and power and in the consolidated forecast balance of production and supply of electrical energy (power ) within the framework of the unified energy system of Russia on subjects of the Russian Federation "(from 17.07.2017 G. № 842) has established indicative prices for electricity and power for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryatia.
As a result, the cost of electrical energy for Buryat producers decreases by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the life of small and medium enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the Republic obivalied the thresholds of Moscow offices in vain attempts to equalize the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydro-power plants on the hangar flowing from Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryatia.
And only this year began the movement.
In March electricity tariffs for the population of the Republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kwh to 3.93 rubles/kwh, or by 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the list of areas of the wholesale market price zones, for which the peculiarities of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established, the turn of industrial consumers has come.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, as the population of the Irkutsk region pays for kilowatt/hour 1.01 rubles.
But nobody dares to name at least an approximate date of new tariff shifts downwards for buryatia.
