In a letter to the head of the company-owned facility, the Scottish branch of GMB demanded that the Mcvitie's respond to the concern that funding would not be put on the modernization of production lines.
Senior organiser Drew Duffy said: "Members of our trade union are deeply concerned that we cannot get clarity from the general manager of the facility on business needs and investment plan for the future of Tolkrossa."
Families have worked here for generations, and the concentration of workers is great in local society and in the Greater Glasgow area; It is the most important pillar of decent work in the territory of high unemployment and social deprivation.
Thus, in terms of jobs, salaries and prosperity, and amid brekzita, rising subsistence and chronic decline in production, the East end of Glasgow is desperately in need of prosperity production at the factory Mcvitie's.
According to the representative of the company Pladis, "the head of the Tolkrosskogo object only yesterday received a letter from the Scottish branch of GMB, and the company will respond immediately, as we appreciate our constant cooperation with employees and representatives Trade union ".
Two months ago we held a regular meeting in Tolkrosse with the staff and representatives of GMB, where a number of issues were openly discussed.
We talked to the staff that as all companies working in the most competitive and unstable economic climate, we are constantly reviewing our actions-and this applies to all our facilities and activities-to remain competitive.
"In recent years we have invested more than 5 million pounds in our Tolkrosskij facility, especially in production lines and improvement of functional indicators."
We are fully aware of the value of Tolkrossa as a production facility, and in case of any changes in the work on this site employees and representatives of the trade union will learn about it first. "
