In Russia there will be two new territories ahead of socio-economic development-"Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decisions of the RF government will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of Tora in the territory of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are defined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is supposed that it will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments to the city, and also create more than 600 new jobs.
In the list of economic activities in which the Tor "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, included crop production, animal husbandry, food production, non-alcoholic Drinks and clothing.
Already now the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on realization of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the lifespan of the company "Abakan Mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Development to create Thor.
The authorities of the Orenburg region also acted in the same way.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk will also be created a territory ahead of socio-economic development.
It will allow to diversify economy of towns, to reduce its dependence on lifespan enterprise of JSC "Ural Steel", and also to create more than 2.3 thousand working places and to attract investments in volume more than 8 Mmilliardov rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new Tor will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, among others, freshwater fish farming, the production of fodder, drugs and medical supplies.
Novotroitsk became the first of the towns Orenburg region, which received the status of Thor.
We remind that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investments to improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for the residents of Tor can be distinguished as follows: income tax in the amount of no more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free Customs Zone, Preferential mode of connection to various infrastructure objects, as well as preferential rates on rent.
